Ethan Jacobson, Senior Software Architect at Nevo,
has developed a profound understanding of the subtle and complex design
issues in highly distributed, web-based systems. During the past 15 years,
he has built the architecture for MediLife, Inc.'s consumer self-care
applications, led the design and implementation of a database abstraction
mechanism for Interleaf, Inc. and contributed to the design of the Atari
7800 ProSystem for General Computer Company. Among his current projects
is the design and implementation of the .NET based metadata-driven
architecture of the Acushnet OASIS mobile sales automation application,
and the development of an application set for the Registrar's Office at
Harvard University, a solution using a three-tiered distributed object
model implemented with Java/CORBA on a combination of data sources.

<p>Mr. Jacobson earned a BS degree in Electrical
Engineering and Computer Science from Princeton University.



